CHAPTER XLIV.

Herennius Bassus replies to Hanno's Speech. Hannibal loses all Hope of recovering Nola by Treachery. [nx-ests the City. Marcellus makes a Sortie. A fieree Engagement follows. Tho Romans retire within the City, the Carthaginians into their Camp. Heavy Rains compel Inaction on 1110 following Day. Hannibal proceeds on the third Day to plunder the Territory about Nola. Marcellus sallies out against him. A general Action ensues.—B.c. 215.
